st findings. These contemporary researchers also break from the past by seeking a more nuanced, contingent, and rigorous theory-based explication of how implementation unfolds. They argue that researchers and practitioners can help improve education policy implementation by not asking simply what works, but rather focusing their attention on what works, for whom, where, when, and why.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEducational changezUnited States. 0aEducational leadershipzUnited States. 0aSchool improvement programszUnited States. 4aEducation : Education Policy and Leadership. 7aEDUCATION / Leadership.2bisacsh1 aAnyon, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoburn, Cynthia E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDatnow, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDumas, Michael J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEvans, Andrea E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGomez, Louis M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHill, Heather C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonig, Meredith I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHonig, Meredith I., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLoeb, Susanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalen, Betty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcEwan, Patrick J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLaughlin, Milbrey W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReiser, Brian J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSmylie, Mark A., 